    <bug_when>2014-01-23 04:16:06 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>EclipseCompiler#run() implements javax.tools.Tool#run(), which has following javadoc:

     * @param in &quot;standard&quot; input; use System.in if null
     * @param out &quot;standard&quot; output; use System.out if null
     * @param err &quot;standard&quot; error; use System.err if null

EclipseCompiler doesn&apos;t take care of this, instead just passes along the parameters err and out. This needs to be fixed.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
